title: PPPP’s Tariq Ali wins PS-48 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Candidate of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Tariq Ali has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-48 Mirpur Khas-4 constituency by securing 66,022 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Inayatullah of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 15,638 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 49.23 per cent in the constituency.
